data.chText: 有很大影响的；有支配力的
data.enText: having a lot of influence on sb/sth

data.chText: 她是本地政坛举足轻重的人物。
data.enText: She is one of the most influential figures in local politics.

data.chText: 委员会左右着政府就业政策的制定。
data.enText: The committee was influential in formulating government policy on employment.

tr: having or exercising influence or power

value.def: Someone or something that is influential has a lot of influence over people or events.

example.ex: It helps to have influential friends.
example.tran: 有几个位高权重的朋友很有好处。

example.ex: ...the influential position of president of the chamber...
example.tran: 很有影响力的议院议长之位

example.ex: He had been influential in shaping economic policy.
example.tran: 他在制定经济政策方面起到了影响。

example.ex: ...one of the most influential books ever written.
